				<div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><table class="infobox" cellspacing="3" style="border-spacing: 3px; width:22em; width:22em;">
<tr>
<th colspan="2" class="" style="text-align:center; font-size:125%; font-weight:bold; background-color: #c9ffd9;">Romance</th>
</tr>
<tr class="">
<th scope="row" style="text-align:left;">Geographic<br />
distribution:</th>
<td class="" style="">Originally <a href="Southern_Europe" title="Southern Europe">Southern Europe</a> and <a href="Africa_(Roman_province)" title="Africa (Roman province)">parts of Northern Africa</a>; now also most of <a href="The_Americas" title="The Americas" class="mw-redirect">America</a>. Official languages of half the countries in <a href="Africa" title="Africa">Africa</a> and parts of <a href="Oceania" title="Oceania">Oceania</a>.</td>
</tr>
<tr class="">
<th scope="row" style="text-align:left;"><a href="Language_family" title="Language family">Linguistic classification</a>:</th>
<td class="" style=""><a href="Indo-European_languages" title="Indo-European languages">Indo-European</a>
<ul style="line-height:100%; margin-left:15px;padding-left:0">
<li><a href="Italic_languages" title="Italic languages">Italic</a>
<ul style="line-height:100%; margin-left:5px;padding-left:0">
<li><b>Romance</b></li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
</td>
</tr>
<tr class="">
<th scope="row" style="text-align:left;">Proto-language:</th>
<td class="" style=""><a href="Vulgar_Latin" title="Vulgar Latin">Vulgar Latin</a></td>
</tr>
<tr class="">
<th scope="row" style="text-align:left;">Subdivisions:</th>
<td class="" style="">
<div><a href="Western_Romance_languages" title="Western Romance languages">Western Romance</a> (or <a href="Italo-Western_languages" title="Italo-Western languages">Italo-Western</a>)</div>
<div><a href="Eastern_Romance_languages" title="Eastern Romance languages">Eastern Romance</a></div>
<div><a href="Sardinian_language" title="Sardinian language">Sardinian</a></div>
</td>
</tr>
<tr class="">
<td colspan="2" class="" style="text-align:center;"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Romance_Languages-World-Map.png" class="image"><img alt="Romance Languages-World-Map.png" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2c/Romance_Languages-World-Map.png/300px-Romance_Languages-World-Map.png" width="300" height="132" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2c/Romance_Languages-World-Map.png/450px-Romance_Languages-World-Map.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2c/Romance_Languages-World-Map.png/600px-Romance_Languages-World-Map.png 2x" /></a><br />
<div style="text-align:left;">Countries where Romance languages are official (dark orange) or national/secondary (light orange)</div>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
